                            <comment id="14566012" author="naoto" created="Fri, 10 Mar 2023 17:02:19 -0800"  >On second thought, having API in j.l.Character class has merits to share the existing mechanism for the character property data which seems better than the ad-hoc property only for Emoji. Also, having an internal I/F may cause the module graph to be changed.</comment>
                            <comment id="14562108" author="naoto" created="Wed, 22 Feb 2023 10:37:16 -0800"  >Probably staring off as an internal interface, say `jdk.internal.util.EmojiProperty` providing Emoji related values. There are other properties currently not supported in the JDK (it only supports General Category), so it can be extended.</comment>
